        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <details>
            <summary>How much does an Canada prep center cost?</summary>
            <p>The cost of Canada prep services can vary widely based on several factors, 
                including the type of product, the specific prep services needed, the volume of products,
                 and the prep service provider you choose.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>What is a Canada prep center?</summary>
            <p>A Canada prep center offers a comprehensive service where they receive and prepare your inventory before shipping
                 it to Canada’s prep fulfillment centers. 
                This service includes tasks such as bubble wrapping, bagging, labeling, packaging, and handling the shipping process..</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>I have more questions, where should I go?</summary>
            <p>We are the largest FBA Prep provider, specializing in temperature-controlled products such as frozen goods, chocolates,
                 and probiotics. Our services include bulk storage, poly bagging, labeling, and strict compliance with Amazon’s meltable 
                 guidelines. With facilities across North America, we ensure your products are stored, prepped, and shipped safely and
                  efficiently.<p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>What is FBA and FBM?</summary>
            <p>Fulfillment of Amazon (FBA) is a service provided by Canada prep center that provides storage, packaging & shipping 
                assistance to sellers whereas Fulfillment by Merchant (FBM) is when sellers choose to list their products
                 on prep center but manage all storage, shipping, customer support manually.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary>How Product Return works from Amazon?</summary>
            <p>Amazon permits customers to return purchased items within a designated return period for a range of reasons, 
                such as receiving a defective or damaged product, selecting an incorrect item, or opting for a different choice.</p>
        </details>
